data.content:
Your code **does not use `Thread.Abort`**, `Thread.Interrupt`, `ThreadAbortException`, or `Thread.ResetAbort`. It only uses `Thread.Start()`, `Thread.Join()`, and `Thread.Sleep()` — all of which work identically in .NET 8 and require no migration.

That said, while not a Thread.Abort concern, you could modernize this to use `Parallel.ForEach` or `Task.WhenAll` for cleaner parallelism:

```csharp
public async Task RunBatchAsync(List<WorkItem> items)
{
    await Parallel.ForEachAsync(items, async (item, ct) =>
    {
        await Task.Run(() => Process(item), ct);
    });
}
```

